description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THIS POST IS FIXED TERM/SECONDMENT FOR 6 MONTHS DUE TO &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PROJECT WORK&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for a part time (22.5 hours per week, details to be agreed) Senior Administration and Resource officer to join the Health Protection Surveillance team based in our offices in Cardiff. The successful candidate will deliver a wide range of administrative functions to assist in the delivery of various projects. This role primarily focuses on the delivery of the convalescent plasma project.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be required to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparing and distributing of a large number of letters associated with the project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Order all necessary stock for the project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as a central point of contact for the team members, agencies and stakeholders, communicating professionally at all times.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will have good problem solving skills and will be able to deal with situations with minimal supervision. A high attention to detail and competency in the use of Word and other Microsoft programmes would be advantageous.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As part of the role, you would be expected to print, label and prepare a large number of letters/packs per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you are self-motivated, with the ability to juggle and prioritise a range of tasks then we would love to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameEric MaljianJob titleBusiness and Operations ManagerEmail addresseric.maljian@wales.nhs.ukTelephone number07899 062728&lt;/p&gt;
